# Python AI Engineering Learning Program - Master Specification

## Program Overview

This is a project-based learning program designed for an experienced engineer transitioning to Python and AI engineering. The learner has extensive engineering knowledge including data science (R), and commercial experience in Objective-C, C++, Ruby, Python, and Java, though not recent Python work.

## Learning Philosophy

- **Learn by doing**: Every concept is taught through building something tangible
- **Visual feedback**: Projects produce visible, interactive results
- **Progressive complexity**: Each project builds on previous knowledge
- **Real-world relevance**: All projects connect to AI engineering applications
- **Code review focus**: Learning is reinforced through detailed feedback and iteration

## Program Structure

### Phase 1: Python Fundamentals Through Visualization (2-3 weeks)
Focus: Modern Python syntax, idioms, and core libraries through visual projects

### Phase 2: ML Foundations with Games (4-6 weeks)
Focus: Machine learning basics, neural networks, and reinforcement learning through interactive applications

### Phase 3: Modern AI Engineering (6-8 weeks)
Focus: LLMs, agents, RAG systems, and production AI engineering

