## Success Metrics

By program completion, you should be able to:
- Write idiomatic, type-safe Python that feels natural
- Build and train neural networks from scratch and with frameworks
- Implement and deploy RAG systems and AI agents
- Debug and optimize Python applications effectively
- Read and contribute to professional Python codebases
- Understand modern AI engineering architecture and practices

## Time Commitment

- **Recommended pace**: 10-15 hours per week
- **Total duration**: 12-17 weeks
- **Project time**: 80% of time spent coding
- **Review/learning**: 20% of time on feedback, reading, research

## Adaptation Guidelines

This program should flex based on your progress:
- Skip or speed through concepts you already know well
- Spend extra time on areas that feel challenging
- Add additional projects if you want deeper practice in an area
- Modify project requirements to align with interests

The goal is mastery, not completion speed. Take the time needed to internalize concepts and build excellent code.
